n generate alpha-keto acid products including pyruvate.", "reasoning": "The user-provided hydrothermal framework explicitly includes pyruvate synthesis on magnetite/greigite, consistent with iron-sulfur world carbon fixation logic feeding early metabolic hubs (Russell et al., 2010; Barge et al., 2022)."}, {"id": "rxn_003", "name": "Spark- and UV-driven formation of HCN from reduced atmospheric feedstocks", "inputs": ["mol_002", "mol_003", "mol_005"], "outputs": ["mol_004"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["TiO2 (anatase/rutile)", "sulfide minerals (molybdenite/stibnite)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "300-350K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "TiO2 photocatalysis with volcanic sulfide mineral context", "aqueous": "true", "other": "UV irradiation or electrical discharge in volcanic surface settings; anoxic"}, "mechanism": "Energetic atmospheric and near-surface processes generate nitriles including HCN, which accumulate in surface waters and shallow vent pools.", "reasoning": "HCN is a central feedstock in classic spark-discharge chemistry and the later cyanosulfidic network; volcanic H2S-rich conditions increase amino-acid precursor diversity and plausibly support nitrile-rich environments (Miller, 1953; Parker et al., 2011; Cleaves, 2012)."}, {"id": "rxn_004", "name": "Photoredox reduction of HCN to formaldehyde via methanimine", "inputs": ["mol_004", "mol_005"], "outputs": ["mol_007", "mol_008"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["sulfide minerals (molybdenite/stibnite)", "TiO2 (anatase/rutile)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "300-350K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "UV photoredox with sulfide-mediated reductive environment", "aqueous": "true", "other": "UV irradiation; cyanosulfidic shallow pool chemistry; H2S as reductant"}, "mechanism": "HCN undergoes reductive homologation to methanimine, which hydrolyzes to formaldehyde under cyanosulfidic photochemistry.", "reasoning": "Ritson and Sutherland described reductive homologation of HCN to formald