 "Avoid implying a direct formamide + H2 surface reduction unless supported by a specific catalytic context."]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_003": 0.72, "rxn_008": 0.95, "rxn_009": 0.8, "rxn_010": 0.58, "rxn_011": 0.93, "rxn_014": 0.88, "rxn_015": 0.85}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.82, "pathway_coherence": 0.89, "environmental_progression": 0.88, "target_achievement": 0.91, "overall_confidence": 0.86, "feedback": "This pathway is coherent and well connected to literature describing formamide as a prebiotic medium and N-formylation of amino acid nitriles as a protective step. The protection-deprotection logic is chemically sensible and addresses a real challenge in aminonitrile persistence. As with P1, the weak point is the oversimplified route to glyceraldehyde. Otherwise this is a strong augmentation of the canonical serine nitrile path.", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_010"], "suggestions": ["Specify whether N-formylation occurs in neat formamide, formamide-rich pools, or drying films.", "Clarify hydrolysis/deprotection conditions to avoid overexposure of serine to destructive heat.", "Expand the homologation chemistry upstream of glyceraldehyde."]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_003": 0.72, "rxn_008": 0.95, "rxn_012": 0.97, "rxn_014": 0.88, "rxn_015": 0.85}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.9, "pathway_coherence": 0.93, "environmental_progression": 0.89, "target_achievement": 0.92, "overall_confidence": 0.91, "feedback": "This is an excellent pathway combining two well-supported modern prebiotic motifs: thiophosphate-enhanced serine nitrile generation and formamide-mediated nitrile protection. It is short, convergent, and mechanistically purposeful. The main improvement needed is better specification of exact UV/redox conditions and clearer differentiation between nitrile formation, protection, and final aqueous hydrolysis environments.", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": [], "suggestions": ["Add the UV and sulf